com.apriori.util

Class Immediate<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apriori.util.Immediate<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of value

    public abstract class Immediate<T>
extends Object
    Like a Future, except it represents a result that is available immediately. Unlike a Variable, it can represent either a successful result value or a cause of failure.

    Its API closely resembles that of ListenableFuture except that, since the value is immediately available, no methods ever block. So methods for determining if the value is complete and those that block until it's complete are unnecessary.
